<B>__{the un trucks}
<A>__{parked in front of the hotel. tutsi refugees file up and are helped on board by un soldiers. paul helps tatiana and the children onto a truck. an argument breaks out towards the back of the convoy. paul rushes toward xavier and benedict who argue.}
<C>__{xavier}
<D>__{they should go one truck at a time. when the first truck gets through to the airport, then the others will follow.}
<C>__{paul}
<D>__{we can't wait. we all go together or not at all.}
<A>__{paul takes matters into his own hands. he locks the doors of the hotel. there is no going back.}
<C>__{paul }
<D>__{it is time to leave. the mille collines is closed.}
<A>__{paul climbs onto the truck. the others follow, some reluctantly. colonel oliver gives the signal. the trucks take off down the driveway.}
